  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering generally involves financial transactions intended to conceal the origins of illegally obtained money. Legal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but typically include:\n\n1. Core elements\n- Concealing source of funds\n- Disguising illegal proceeds\n- Attempting to make illicit money appear legitimate\n\n2. Common legal components\n- Transforming criminal proceeds\n- Moving money through complex transactions\n- Attempting to integrate illegal funds into legal financial systems\n\n3. Typical prohibited activities\n- Structuring cash deposits\n- Using shell companies\n- International wire transfers\n- Cryptocurrency transactions\n- Complex financial exchanges\n\n4. Jurisdictional variations\n- United States: Bank Secrecy Act\n- European Union: Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- International standards via Financial Action Task Force (FATF)\n\n5. Potential criminal penalties\n- Significant financial fines\n- Imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n\nThe specific legal definitions can have nuanced differences depending on local statutes and regulations.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering definitions?",
